# ── Aurora & Ash Tattoo · Project Constitution ─────────────────────────────
#
# This file is the single source of truth for every AI agent working on this
# codebase.  Violating a rule marked MANDATORY will block a PR from being
# merged.  Rules marked STANDARD represent the team's collective taste and
# should only be broken with an explicit, commented reason.

# ── 1. PROJECT IDENTITY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

name:              Aurora & Ash Tattoo
type:              Luxury tattoo-studio website
repo-root:         aurora-ash-tattoo/
slug:              aurora-ash

# ── 2. TECH STACK (locked versions) ────────────────────────────────────────

runtime:           Node.js ≥ 20
package-manager:   npm
framework:         Next.js 16.2.4  (App Router)
cms:               Payload CMS 3.84.1
database:          SQLite  (libsql via @libsql/client)
language:          TypeScript 5.x  — strict: true  MANDATORY
styles:            Tailwind CSS 4.2.4  +  PostCSS 8  +  Autoprefixer 10
animation:         Framer Motion 12.38.0
lint:              ESLint 9  (eslint-config-next 16.2.4)
images:            Sharp 0.34.5  (server-side optimisation)
fonts:             Playfair Display  (headings)  +  Inter  (body)

# ── 3. SECURITY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3.1  SECRETS  MANDATORY
     • Never hard-code secrets.  All secrets live in .env.local (git-ignored).
     • Required env vars:
         PAYLOAD_SECRET          — ≥ 32-char random string; used for JWT signing
         DATABASE_URI            — SQLite connection string (default: file:./payload.db)
         NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL    — public-facing URL (default: http://localhost:3000)
     • .env.local MUST be listed in .gitignore.  Confirm before every commit.

3.2  AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION  MANDATORY
     • Payload CMS handles auth (JWT-based, httpOnly cookie).
     • Two roles: admin | artist  (defined in access.ts).
     • Access-control functions must be re-used from access.ts — never
       duplicate role logic inline.
     • Artists can only manage their own linked artist profile and their
       own works.  Admin-only actions: user creation, user deletion, style
       management, page management.
     • Public routes (/, /portfolio/*, /api/media/*) must remain readable
       without authentication.

3.3  INPUT VALIDATION  MANDATORY
     • All user-submitted forms (inquiries, newsletter, contact) must
       validate on both client AND server.
     • Sanitise free-text fields before rendering — Payload's Lexical
       editor output is HTML, which must be treated as potentially unsafe
       unless explicitly trusted.
     • File uploads: restrict to MIME types declared in payload.config.ts
       (jpeg, png, webp, avif, svg+xml).  Maximum file size: 10 MB.

3.4  CSRF / XSS  MANDATORY
     • Payload's built-in CSRF protection is enabled — do not disable.
     • Never use dangerouslySetInnerHTML on user-supplied content without
       a sanitisation layer.
     • CSP headers should be configured in next.config.mjs for production.

3.5  DATA PRIVACY  STANDARD
     • Inquiry collection stores PII (name, email, telegram) — access to
       the inquiries collection is restricted to admin role only.
     • Age confirmation (18+) and privacy consent are required fields on
       every inquiry submission.

# ── 4. TYPESCRIPT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

4.1  STRICT MODE  MANDATORY
     • tsconfig.json has "strict": true — never weaken it.
     • Use const for immutable bindings, let only when reassignment is needed.
     • NEVER use var.  NEVER use any — prefer unknown and type guards.
     • Prefer type over interface for props shapes; use interface for
       class-like structures that benefit from declaration merging.

4.2  PATH ALIASES
     • @/  maps to the project root (aurora-ash-tattoo/).
     • @payload-config  maps to ./payload.config.ts.
     • Always use aliases for internal imports — no relative ../../ chains.

4.3  TYPE GENERATION
     • Payload auto-generates payload-types.ts — never edit it by hand.
     • Run npm run generate:types after schema changes.

# ── 5. CSS & STYLING ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

5.1  CUSTOM PROPERTIES  MANDATORY
     • All colours, spacing, typography scales, and transition durations
       must be defined as CSS custom properties in a global theme file.
     • Never use magic numbers — add a comment explaining non-obvious values
       (e.g. /* 0.618 — golden-ratio spacing */).

5.2  TAILWIND USAGE
     • Tailwind utility classes are the primary styling method.
     • Use Tailwind's arbitrary-value syntax (w-[320px]) sparingly — prefer
       design-token-aligned values.
     • Custom component classes (e.g. .btn--primary) may use @apply in
       component-level CSS modules when a utility pattern repeats ≥ 3 times.

5.3  BEM NAMING  STANDARD
     • Custom CSS classes follow BEM: .block__element--modifier.
     • Blocks map to React components (e.g. .artist-card).
     • Elements are children (e.g. .artist-card__portrait).
     • Modifiers are states/variants (e.g. .artist-card--featured).

5.4  MOBILE-FIRST  MANDATORY
     • Base styles target viewports < 768 px.
     • Use min-width media queries (Tailwind's md:, lg:, xl: prefixes).
     • Test every component at 375 px, 768 px, 1024 px, and 1440 px.

# ── 6. ANIMATION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

6.1  PERFORMANCE  MANDATORY
     • All animations must target only compositor-friendly properties:
       opacity, transform (translate, scale, rotate).  Never animate
       width, height, top, left, margin, or padding.
     • CSS transitions are preferred over JS-driven animations for hover
       states and simple entrances.
     • Framer Motion is reserved for scroll-linked animations, page
       transitions, and complex gesture-driven interactions.
     • Use will-change sparingly and only on elements that will animate
       within the next 200 ms.

# ── 7. REACT / NEXT.JS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

7.1  COMPONENT ARCHITECTURE  STANDARD
     • Every component has a single responsibility.  If a component
       exceeds ~200 lines, extract sub-components.
     • File naming: PascalCase for components (ArtistCard.tsx),
       camelCase for utilities (formatDate.ts).
     • Co-locate component tests and styles: ArtistCard.tsx,
       ArtistCard.test.tsx, ArtistCard.module.css live in the same folder.

7.2  SERVER vs CLIENT COMPONENTS
     • Default to Server Components.  Add 'use client' only when the
       component uses hooks, event handlers, or browser-only APIs.
     • Fetch data on the server via Payload's local API — never expose
       the Payload REST endpoint publicly unless absolutely necessary.

7.3  METADATA & SEO  MANDATORY
     • Every route must export a metadata object (or use generateMetadata).
     • Open Graph images are required for all artist pages and the home page.
     • Alt text is mandatory on every <Image> component.

# ── 8. PAYLOAD CMS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

8.1  COLLECTION STRUCTURE
     • collections: users, media, styles, artists, works, pages, inquiries
     • globals:     siteSettings
     • Versioning with drafts is enabled on artists, works, and pages.

8.2  ACCESS CONTROL
     • All access rules are centralized in access.ts.
     • New collections MUST declare explicit access.create / read /
       update / delete — never rely on Payload defaults.

8.3  HOOKS
     • beforeChange hooks are used for slug generation and
       automatic uploadedBy assignment.
     • Rate-limiting on the inquiries collection (create operation)
       must be implemented before production launch.

8.4  MEDIA
     • Upload directory: public/media/
     • Image sizes generated: thumbnail (400×400), card (800w),
       feature (1200w), hero (1920w).
     • Images from external sources must be downloaded and served locally —
       no hotlinking.

# ── 9. PERFORMANCE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

9.1  CORE WEB VITALS  MANDATORY
     • LCP < 2.5 s — prioritise hero images with fetchpriority="high".
     • CLS < 0.1  — always set explicit width/height on images.
     • INP < 200 ms — avoid long tasks; defer non-critical scripts.

9.2  IMAGES
     • Use Next.js <Image> component for all raster images.
     • Provide sizes prop for responsive image selection.
     • Use placeholder="blur" with a base64 blurDataURL for above-the-fold images.

9.3  BUNDLE SIZE
     • No dependency added without a documented reason.  Prefer native
       APIs over libraries (e.g. Intl.DateTimeFormat instead of dayjs).
     • Use next/dynamic with ssr: false for heavy client-only components
       (maps, complex animations).

# ── 10. ACCESSIBILITY (a11y) ───────────────────────────────────────────────

10.1  MANDATORY
     • Semantic HTML: use <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>,
       <aside>, <footer> — not <div> soup.
     • All interactive elements must be keyboard-accessible (Tab, Enter, Escape).
     • Focus indicators must be visible (never use outline: none without
       a replacement style).
     • aria-label on all icon-only buttons and links.
     • Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for body text, ≥ 3:1 for large text.

10.2  STANDARD
     • Prefers-reduced-motion: disable all non-essential animations when
       the user's OS setting is active.
     • Form inputs must have associated <label> elements.

# ── 11. CODE QUALITY ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

11.1  LINTING  MANDATORY
     • ESLint 9 with eslint-config-next (core-web-vitals + typescript).
     • Run npm run lint before every commit.  Zero warnings allowed.

11.2  FORMATTING
     • Indentation: 2 spaces.  No tabs.
     • Semicolons: required.
     • Trailing commas: always (ES5).
     • Quotes: single quotes for JSX/TS, double for JSX props.

11.3  COMMENTS
     • Explain WHY, not WHAT.  The code should be self-documenting for
       the "what".
     • Non-obvious values must have an inline comment explaining their
       derivation (e.g. /* 0.618 — golden ratio for card aspect */).

# ── 12. ENVIRONMENT & DEPLOYMENT ───────────────────────────────────────────

12.1  LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
     • npm run dev       — starts Next.js + Payload on :3000
     • npm run devsafe   — cleans .next cache before starting
     • npm run payload   — Payload CLI
     • npm run seed      — opens seed endpoint in browser

12.2  BUILD
     • npm run build     — Next.js production build
     • TypeScript errors are fatal — the build WILL fail on type errors.
     • All environment variables required at build time must be prefixed
       with NEXT_PUBLIC_ or provided in .env.production.

12.3  PRODUCTION
     • npm run start     — starts the production server
     • PAYLOAD_SECRET must be a strong, unique value per environment.
     • Database file (payload.db) must be backed up regularly.
     • Enable Payload's rate-limiter plugin before launch.

# ── 13. TESTING ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

13.1  STANDARD
     • Critical paths (inquiry submission, auth flow, artist page render)
       should have integration tests.
     • Component tests for reusable UI primitives (Button, Modal, Accordion).
     • Access-control functions in access.ts must have unit tests.
     • Use Playwright or Cypress for E2E; Vitest + React Testing Library
       for unit/component tests.

# ── 14. VERSION CONTROL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

14.1  MANDATORY
     • .gitignore must include: .env.local, .next/, payload.db, node_modules/,
       tsconfig.tsbuildinfo.
     • Never commit generated files (payload-types.ts is an exception — it
       is committed so CI/CD can type-check without a running Payload instance).
     • Commit messages: imperative mood, ≤ 72 chars for subject, blank line
       before body.  Prefix with scope when helpful (feat:, fix:, chore:).

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# End of .clinerules — Aurora & Ash Tattoo
